Timmy dislikes social pecking orders. he hates those who hold leadership positions, and disapproves of alliance with imperial institutions.

If imprisoned, he will be uncooperative with his captors.
traits.name: anarchist

traits.description:
Timmy wants to be led by others, and dislikes holding authority himself.

If imprisoned, he will be quite cooperative with his captors.
traits.name: servile

traits.description: Timmy dampens nearby psychic phenomena and is immensely resistant to direct psychic interference.
traits.name: psychicblank

traits.description: Timmy has an innate connection to the archotechs. This connection might awaken if he experiences something sufficiently grand or terrible, permanently transforming him into a powerful psycaster.
traits.name: latentpsychic

traits.description: Timmy has an innate connection to the archotechs. This connection might awaken if he experiences something sufficiently grand or terrible, permanently transforming him into a powerful psycaster.
traits.name: latentpsychic

traits.description: Timmy has an innate connection to the archotechs. This connection might awaken if he experiences something sufficiently grand or terrible, permanently transforming him into a powerful psycaster.
traits.name: latentpsychic

traits.description: Timmy has an innate connection to the archotechs. This connection might awaken if he experiences something sufficiently grand or terrible, permanently transforming him into a powerful psycaster.
traits.name: latentpsychic

traits.description: Timmy has an innate connection to the archotechs. This connection might awaken if he experiences something sufficiently grand or terrible, permanently transforming him into a powerful psycaster.
traits.name: latentpsychic

traits.description: Timmy has an innate connection to the archotechs. This connection might awaken if he experiences something sufficiently grand or terrible, permanently transforming him into a powerful psycaster.
traits.name: latentpsychic

traits.description: Timmy is a powerful psycaster with exceptional sensitivity to perturbations in the psychic field.
traits.name: awakenedaugur

traits.description: Timmy can use any meditation type. he gains psyfocus faster from meditating, and meditating takes care of his basic needs.
traits.name: awakenedchanshi

traits.description: Timmy is capable of using nearly any 1st-level psycast without expending psyfocus, so long as he has enough psyfocus to cast it in the first place.
traits.name: awakeneddeluge

traits.description: Timmy is an exceptionally versatile psycaster with a wide array of abilities. he may also develop up to two more transcendences than other awakened psychics.
traits.name: awakenederudite

traits.description: Timmy grows physically and mentally stronger with every psycast he learns.
traits.name: awakenedincarnate

traits.description: Timmy exudes an aura that empowers psycasting.
traits.name: awakenedluminary

traits.description: Timmy is a powerful psycaster, capable of passively generating psyfocus.
traits.name: awakenedmantraist

traits.description: Once a day, Timmy can draw upon a confluence of power within the psychic field, greatly enhancing his psycasting for an hour. Outside of this period, he finds psycasting requires more psyfocus.
traits.name: awakenedperennial

traits.description: Timmy is a powerful psycaster with a vastly improved neural heat capacity and an exceptionally disciplined mind.
traits.name: awakenedsage

traits.description: Timmy draws psyfocus from consuming food.
traits.name: awakenedsiphoner

traits.description: Timmy reinforces his body with accumulated psyfocus, improving his capabilities and defenses.
traits.name: awakenedtitan

traits.description: Instead of harming him, damage taken by Timmy depletes his psyfocus (at a ratio of 4.5 damage to 1% psyfocus).
traits.name: awakenedundying

traits.description: Timmy hovers, negating movement penalties from the terrain, and he also gains armor based on the current wind level. While meditating, he causes the wind to howl.
traits.name: psychicalbatross

traits.description: Timmy grows in size and strength over time. This has no upper limit, and increases his strength, speed, and (up to a point) damage resistance; however, it also makes his easier to hit and worse at avoiding traps.
traits.name: psychicanaconda

traits.description: Every 1000% psyfocus Timmy spends summons an anima tree somewhere nearby. If he dies, he will instantly respawn at a nearby anima tree, killing the tree.
traits.name: psychicanimalume

traits.description: Timmy can exert a form of mind control on mechanoids. When he affects mechanoids with a psycast, they may become allied with him for up to an hour. The heavier the mech, the less likely this is to work.
traits.name: psychicapocriton

traits.description: Timmy warps nearby electromagnetic currents. he inflicts EMPs via attacks and psycasts, is immune to EMPs himself, and has improved sight. This control over electric currents even extends to his own organs, protecting him against heart attacks and some forms of coma.
traits.name: psychicarcturan

traits.description: Aided by a psychic sense, Timmy can easily visualize how to assemble or break down objects in his immediate vicinity. his psychic sensitivity increases up the rate at which he works with plants and buildings, and affects how much damage he does to buildings.
traits.name: psychicbeaver

traits.description: Word psycasts used by Timmy cost +7.5% psyfocus, but affect all nearby valid targets. The radius of this effect is equal to twice his psylink level.
traits.name: psychicbellbird

traits.description: Timmy is surrounded by a protective immaterial presence, which attacks nearby foes and attempts to divert incoming blows.
traits.name: psychicbluejay

traits.description: Timmy generates rock chunks with each psycast (and sometimes also makes more valuable metallic resources). On using a psycast of the highest level, there is a 10% chance a meteorite will fall somewhere nearby.
traits.name: psychicbouldermit

traits.description: Timmy emits a healing skipshield while meditating. The healing applies to everything in its radius, not just his allies.
traits.name: psychicbowerbird

traits.description: Timmy has a far-reaching psychic influence that gradually improves relations with other factions.
traits.name: psychicbudgie

traits.description: Word psycasts used by Timmy have a profound influence on the target, breaking unwavering loyalty, reducing resistance, and altering mood and certainty.
traits.name: psychiccanary

traits.description: Timmy deals 2.2x damage with persona weapons, further increased by his own psychic sensitivity.
traits.name: psychiccassowary

traits.description: Timmy is a font of genius. he passively contributes to research at a rate scaling with his psychic sensitivity; if no research is currently underway, he instead gradually increases in skill and psyfocus.
traits.name: psychiccockatiel

traits.description: Timmy regenerates from wounds, even permanent ones, unnaturally fast. he can even come back from death, taking somewhere between 3-15 days.
traits.name: psychiccockroach

traits.description: While in water, Timmy moves faster and heals rapidly.
traits.name: psychiccranchiid

traits.description: Timmy moves with unearthly grace. he can walk with surety in the most treacherous bog, and evade even the fastest blows with ease.
traits.name: psychiccrane

traits.description: Timmy psychically influences others to love him more than almost anything else in existence.
traits.name: psychiccuckoo

traits.description:
Timmy repels vectors of harm on an abstract, indirect level. his mere existence has a 50% chance to prevent many kinds of bad events from happening.

Has no effect on events that occur as part of quests.
traits.name: deimaticpsychic

traits.description: Timmy is all but immune to high temperatures. In close-range combat, he repeatedly unleashes flame novas, and his psycasts drench hostile entities and structures in chemfuel.
traits.name: psychicdiabolus

traits.description: Timmy emits a continuous psychic soothe. his psycasts remove mental breaks from anyone affected.
traits.name: psychicdove

traits.description: Anyone whom Timmy kills is shortly thereafter raised in his service. This second life only lasts for three days; psychically deaf individuals, as well as those who are already under this effect, cannot be raised in this way.
traits.name: duloticpsychic

traits.description: Timmy radiates an aura of pain, and is unable to feel it himself. Foes who stay within the aura for too long also begin to lose consciousness.
traits.name: psychicechinoid

traits.description: Timmy regulates ambient temperature, enabling his allies to survive extreme heat or cold, and protecting them from fire.
traits.name: psychiceiderduck

traits.description: Timmy emanates electrical disturbances, charging nearby batteries, calling lightning on nearby foes with each psycast, and sending EMPs through anything he hits in melee.
traits.name: psychicelectrophorus

traits.description: Whenever Timmy undergoes an event that would awaken a latent psychic, a man in black appears. If he fulfills a condition that would awaken a latent psychic, there is a persistent but very small chance for men in black to appear nearby.
traits.name: psychicemperorpenguin

traits.description: Timmy ages so slowly as to be immortal. This effect also prevents him from developing cancer or geriatric diseases, and it reduces his reliance on food and rest.
traits.name: evergreenpsychic

traits.description: Timmy generates unique solar pinholes with each psycast - the light they emit debilitates foes that get too close. he can also see just fine in the dark, and is sustained by an exotic process akin to photosynthesis, greatly slowing his hunger so long as he is in bright light.
traits.name: psychicfirefly

traits.description: Timmy is favored by the flame. he is all but immune to high temperatures. While meditating, he emanates heat. his psycasts can set nearby foes ablaze and inflict heatstroke on the victims; when he strikes, his victims are scalded.
traits.name: psychicfirehawk

traits.description: Timmy is immune to fire, poison, and most environmental phenomena.
traits.name: psychicflamingo

traits.description: Timmy can induce sudden and unnatural movements in his body, making him faster and better at dodging, allowing him to travel much farther with jump abilities, and even allowing him to leap great distances under his own power.
traits.name: psychicfodiator

traits.description:
Timmy has had his entire body replaced and augmented by a cyber-organic, archite-empowered material. he no longer bleeds, surgeries cannot fail on him, and his bodily functions are greatly enhanced.

his psychic potential has been stymied as a result of this change; he can no longer gain new transcendences.
traits.name: fossilizedpsychic

traits.description: Timmy can infrequently generate and fire arcing explosive projectiles over extreme distances.
traits.name: psychicfulmar

traits.description: Timmy causes ruptures in the fabric of space whenever he uses a skip psycast, damaging everything around the endpoint. The radius improves with his psylink level, up to level 6.
traits.name: psychicglowworm

traits.description: Timmy is immune to the harmful effects of most gases. he turns invisible while surrounded by gas, and his psycasts skip particulate into affected foes' eyes.
traits.name: psychicgnat

traits.description: Once a day, every day, Timmy regenerates towards a state of perfect health, becomes immune to the next instance of damage taken, and experiences a brief burst of euphoria. Even his worn apparel and wielded weapons are partially repaired each time this occurs.
traits.name: psychicgoldfinch

traits.description: Timmy is a giant among psycasters, boasting massively expanded psychic sensitivity.
traits.name: haastianpsychic

traits.description: Timmy can eat corpses to gain some of their skill experience, as well as potentially heal himself of an injury or ailment. The chance to heal scales with the corpse's body size. Moreover, he defers incoming damage to nearby corpses.
traits.name: psychicharbinger

traits.description: Timmy moves faster, and has doubled range with skip psycasts.
traits.name: psychicheron

traits.description: Timmy produces food as a byproduct of psycasting. This ability seems to work on a small but constant level within his own body, helping sustain him.
traits.name: psychichoneybee

traits.description: Timmy can emit neural heat in the form of blasts of explosive energy, even while he is performing other tasks. This attack's range scales with his psychic sensitivity.
traits.name: psychichornet

traits.description: Timmy becomes invisible if he hasn't attacked or cast an ability recently.
traits.name: psychichummingbird

traits.description: Timmy has enhanced eyesight. he never gets bored of watching the stars, and using the telescope for long enough can cause a good event to occur.
traits.name: psychicindigobunting

traits.description: Timmy accelerates the growth of nearby plants and causes them to entangle nearby foes.
traits.name: psychicivy

traits.description: As Timmy meditates, he gets closer to creating a random good event.
traits.name: psychicjackdaw

traits.description: Timmy gains experience in each skill when psycasting or meditating.
traits.name: psychickea

traits.description: Timmy has impeccable accuracy - he nearly always hits his intended target, and can find the weakest spot in virtually any armor.
traits.name: psychickingfisher

traits.description: Timmy drains the life from nearby plants to replenish his own vitality, and he siphons psyfocus over time from nearby hostile psycasters.
traits.name: psychicknapweed

traits.description: Timmy inflicts heightened regeneration, toughness, and disease resistance on nearby allies.
traits.name: psychicladybug

traits.description: Timmy periodically skips high-quality meals to his own location. While meditating, his meditation focus gain rate speeds up this process.
traits.name: psychicleghorn

traits.description: Every 24 hours, Timmy manifests random allies - the higher his psychic sensitivity, the more allies are created. They're fragile and will disappear after 24 hours, but they're more psychically sensitive, and they don't need to eat or sleep.
traits.name: psychiclocust

traits.description: Timmy is a temporary manifestation and will soon disappear.
traits.name: psychiclocustspawn

traits.description: Timmy manifests a duplicate of himself. If it dies, he will recreate it after a delay, sped up by expending psyfocus or meditating. Artificial body parts are not duplicated.
traits.name: psychiclovebug

traits.description:
Timmy is a doppelganger of another entity. If slain, he will disappear and later respawn from the original.

It is not possible to remove any artificial body parts he may have.
traits.name: psychicdoppelganger

traits.description: Timmy manifests additional rewards when a quest is completed.
traits.name: psychicmagpie

traits.description: Timmy is subject to a bizarre temporal distortion, which enables him to sleep and meditate faster. It also makes his ability cooldowns recover three times as fast.
traits.name: psychicmayfly

traits.description: Timmy has an incredibly powerful mind, and he emits a cerebral effect that stimulates learning and improves psychic sensitivity.
traits.name: psychicmeerkat

traits.description: Timmy shrinks after spending enough time meditating. In this state, he is invisible to the naked eye and can move through ordinarily impassable obstacles. he returns to normal size on attacking or casting an ability.
traits.name: psychicmite

traits.description:
Timmy removes blood from anyone affected by his psycasts, restoring his own body and hemogen based on the amount of blood removed. This effect cannot kill directly, as it will never bring a victim's blood loss above 50%.

Additionally, he cannot lose blood from open injuries.
traits.name: psychicmosquito

traits.description: Timmy gains psyfocus from the act of eating, and ingesting enough nutrition may produce a random serum.
traits.name: psychicmusang

traits.description: Timmy gains experience by psychically copying the skills of nearby higher-leveled individuals. he may also rarely learn psycasts from other psycasters by conversing with them.
traits.name: psychichillmynah

traits.description: Timmy is a better speaker and regains all but the last 10% of psyfocus spent on Word psycasts.
traits.name: psychicnightingale

traits.description: Timmy becomes more physically and psychically powerful while in the dark, but wilts in the light. Becoming inspired or entering a mental break will always coincide with an eclipse.
traits.name: psychicnoctule

traits.description: Timmy gains armor and neural heat recovery rate as it gets colder.
traits.name: psychicnotothen

traits.description: Whenever Timmy psycasts, it creates a zone at the target's position in which his cognition and psychic sensitivity are enhanced. Only one such zone may exist at any time.
traits.name: psychicoilbird

traits.description:
Whenever Timmy psycasts, nearby plants grow faster, and nearby non-hostile buildings are repaired. The effect scales with his psychic sensitivity.

Psycasting will also heal one random injury from a nearby random pawn; the heal's strength scales with the recipient's psychic sensitivity.
traits.name: psychicorbweaver

traits.description: While in water, Timmy moves faster and is protected from damage. Blasts of water emit from the location of his psycasts.
traits.name: psychicorca

traits.description: Timmy exudes a protective presence, flatly reducing the damage nearby allies take and slowing their fatigue.
traits.name: psychicosprey

traits.description:
Timmy intermittently psychically tames a random animal. This effect can occur over long distances, and its frequency is based on his psychic sensitivity.

When he affects an animal with a psycast, its health is either boosted (if non-hostile) or impaired (if hostile).
traits.name: psychicoxpecker

traits.description: Timmy exudes an aura which improves the vision of allies near him and makes everything it touches look gorgeous.
traits.name: psychicpeacock

traits.description: Timmy can see, attack, and cast abilities from much further away.
traits.name: psychicpelican

traits.description: Timmy has a 40% chance to stun anyone he damages or affects with a psycast. The duration scales with the victim's psychic sensitivity.
traits.name: psychicperegrine

traits.description: Timmy receives detailed extrasensory impressions of his surroundings. This new mode of perception increases dramatically in potency during meditation or psycasting.
traits.name: psychicpipistrelle

traits.description: Timmy is immune to most forms of toxicity, which includes chemical overdoses, addictions, and dependencies; food poisoning; and, to a meager extent, disease. he can cure someone of any such afflictions (except a genetic chemical dependency) by affecting them with a psycast.
traits.name: psychicpitohui

traits.description: Timmy is heavily resistant to disease and toxins. While meditating, he reshapes the surrounding terrain, drying, fertilizing, and unpolluting it.
traits.name: psychicpolux

traits.description: Timmy can survive for long periods of time without air, food, water, rest, or fun, and he emits an effect that partially alleviates these needs in others as well.
traits.name: psychicpoorwill

traits.description: When Timmy is happy, those near him gain a variety of benefits; when he is sad, nearby foes are demoralized and aggravated.
traits.name: psychicptarmigan

traits.description: Timmy constructively shapes inanimate material around himself. his worn and wielded equipment is repaired over time. There is a small chance, while meditating, for part of his gear to improve in quality, or for the spontaneous creation of a high-quality book or sculpture.
traits.name: psychicquahog

traits.description: Timmy is surrounded by a field of selectively weakened gravity, allowing him and nearby allies to hover (allowing them to ignore terrain movement penalties), and preventing them from triggering traps.
traits.name: psychicquelea

traits.description: Timmy broadcasts a psychic serenity detectable by animals, improving his interactions with them, preventing them from harming him, and even causing his psycasts to cure affected animals' scaria.
traits.name: psychicquokka

traits.description: Timmy sometimes receives extrasensory visions of distant places and the near future, which he leverages to reveal good events afterward.
traits.name: psychicraven

traits.description: Timmy moves faster and has an esoteric sense that randomly points him toward objects of interest in the wilderness. This sense is useful for finding treasure while traveling in a moving caravan.
traits.name: psychicrobin

traits.description: Timmy derives more usable material from plants, animals, and mining.
traits.name: psychicrook

traits.description: Timmy is surrounded by a barrier which transforms incoming damage into neural heat. If he overloads his neural heat limit, the barrier will vanish for a day, though it can be regenerated far faster via meditation.
traits.name: psychicscarab

traits.description: Timmy produces luciferium by psycasting.
traits.name: scarletpsychic

traits.description: Timmy has a vast "extradimensional" storage achieved through the use of a personal skipgate system. When he meditates, random items may be added to this storage.
traits.name: psychicscrubjay

traits.description: Timmy is favored by the cold. he is all but immune to cold temperatures. While meditating, he saps heat from the environment. his very presence chills his foes; when he strikes, his victims suffer from hypothermia.
traits.name: seaicepsychic

traits.description: Timmy can manipulate the weather. he also hovers, allowing him to ignore the pathing costs of terrain.
traits.name: psychicshearwater

traits.description: Timmy has a chance to cause good events to occur on killing another person. he also gains psyfocus from killing other beings.
traits.name: psychicshrike

traits.description: Timmy summons an insect hive every time he spends 20% psyfocus, and his presence pacifies all but the largest insectoids. A pacified insectoid behaves like a wild animal, though it doesn't wander very far, and even if it was originally protecting a hive it will no longer take care of it.
traits.name: psychicspelopede

traits.description: Timmy has a 75% chance to avoid damage. Even when he is struck, the blow glances.
traits.name: psychicstoat

traits.description: Every 1000% psyfocus Timmy spends causes another entity to appear somewhere nearby. This new entity is allied with him and comes from a similar background.
traits.name: psychicstork

traits.description: Timmy has a chance to inflict madness upon foes he affects with psycasts. More psychically sensitive victims are more vulnerable, but psylink levels reduce susceptibility to the effect.
traits.name: psychicstrix

traits.description: Timmy is physically, mentally, and psychically empowered by being in a romantic relationship (or unconditionally, if aromantic). his romantic partners and bonded animals receive a physical and mood buff too.
traits.name: psychicswan

traits.description: While Timmy has no neural heat, his movement speed is vastly increased.
traits.name: psychicswift

traits.description: Timmy gains various physical qualities based on his artistic skill.
traits.name: psychictanager

traits.description: Timmy deals high damage to buildings and mines much faster. Additionally, enemy buildings near the locus of his psycasts take high damage; higher-level psycasts result in a wider radius.
traits.name: psychictermite

traits.description: While on a caravan, Timmy covers impossible distances in mere moments.
traits.name: psychicarctictern

traits.description: Timmy augments his melee attacks with skipgates that excise material from the victim, dealing bonus damage that ignores armor and most forms of damage resistance.
traits.name: psychicthrumbo

traits.description: Timmy turns invisible, phases through obstacles, and moves faster for a short while after being hit (even if the hit did no damage).
traits.name: psychictouch-me-not

traits.description: Timmy makes nearby foes more vulnerable to caustic or toxic agents. When harmed, he poisons nearby enemies, with a small chance to inflict acid burn.
traits.name: psychictoxbuzzard

traits.description: Timmy grows in size over time, making him more physically powerful. Spending psyfocus reverses this transformation to some extent.
traits.name: psychicuhu

traits.description: Random corpses appear near Timmy as he spends psyfocus.
traits.name: psychicvulture

traits.description: Timmy benefits from weaker versions of multiple inspirations at once. Those affected by his psycasts may become inspired as well.
traits.name: psychicsedgewarbler

traits.description: Timmy periodically skips psychically tamed animals of a specific type to his location. This effect occurs faster while meditating. New animals won't be summoned if doing so would cause the sum body size of all current ones to exceed twice his psylink level.
traits.name: psychicwarqueen

traits.description: Timmy has supernatural craftsmanship. his creations are a quality level higher and there is a 50% chance that any item with quality that he creates is duplicated.
traits.name: psychicweaverbird

traits.description: A walking portent of death, Timmy terrifies foes in a vast radius, and those closer to him may even be struck by an uncontrollable urge to flee. he is also nearly immune to stress.
traits.name: psychicwhalehead

traits.description: Timmy can pass through solid obstacles while his psyfocus is greater than 35%.
traits.name: psychicwoodpecker

traits.description: Timmy is supernaturally gifted at healing. he heals anyone he tends to and always succeeds at surgery. he also somehow acquires herbal medicine after spending 10% psyfocus or meditating for long enough.
traits.name: psychicxerigium

traits.description: Timmy can focus to generate bolts of energy which spring towards a targeted foe.
traits.name: psychicyellowjacket

traits.description:
When another psycaster or latent psychic dies nearby, Timmy partakes of their dissipating psychic thalergy and accumulates a 'hoard' of energy. This energy strengthens his psycasting and health, while also shielding him from harm. However, the energy lessens whenever it prevents damage. More powerful psycasters grant more energy.

he also cannot be directly affected by his enemies' psycasts.
traits.name: psychicdragon

traits.description: Timmy is more thought than flesh. his physical and mental attributes are greatly amplified by his psychic sensitivity, and his psychic potency is further boosted by the total psylink level of all nearby psycasters.
traits.name: psychicegregore

traits.description: Timmy can strip the psychic sensitivity from others. A second application of this ability kills the victim, extracting some of their psylinks. Awakened psychics cannot be killed by this ability.
traits.name: psychicerinys

traits.description: Ordinary food does little for Timmy, but eating a psycaster will fully sate him for a long while as well as possibly grant a psylink level. On eating the corpse of a fellow awakened or transcendent psychic, he will assimilate all of their awakenings and up to one of their transcendences.
traits.name: psychicharpy

traits.description: Timmy gains increasing potency as a psycaster the longer he lives, develops a new awakening every six years, and gradually develops further transcendent powers over the course of his lifetime.
traits.name: psychicleviathan

traits.description: Timmy can bring the dead back to life, though each beneficiary must spend at least 24 hours alive before this power can be used on them again. If he dies, he will automatically cast it on himself.
traits.name: psychicphoenix

traits.description: Allies near Timmy are invulnerable to direct harm, but almost totally unable to deal direct damage. he experiences a less pronounced version of the effects, and can be harmed. On death, he will pass this ability on to another of the same faction.
traits.name: psychicseraph

traits.description: Timmy can assert permanent mental control over others. The cooldown scales with the victim's market value.
traits.name: psychicsiren

traits.description: Timmy can grant psylink levels to others. This power always succeeds on non-psycasters, but is likelier to fail the more psylink levels the target has. A target who fails three times dies.
traits.name: psychicsphinx

traits.description: Timmy can start others on the path to psychic awakening, induce awakening in a latent psychic, or even grant a second awakening to another.
traits.name: psychicthunderbird

traits.description: When Timmy is slain, he will transfer his consciousness into someone else, replacing their mind with his own. For 24 hours afterward, he will be invulnerable to anything other than persona weapons, but will not be able to transfer to a new body.
traits.name: psychicwraith

traits.description: Timmy can call down destructive pillars of pulverizing force. he accumulates the energy to do so passively, but can speed this process up by meditating. he may also manifest an even more destructive effect, potent enough to obliterate cities, but this requires many days of meditation to charge.
traits.name: psychicziz

traits.description: Timmy is much more strongly affected by the beauty (or ugliness) of his surroundings and fellow persons.
traits.name: aestheticist

traits.description: Timmy might be fine with tame animals, but few things are more terrifying to him than wild or insane animals. he is prone to uncontrollable panic if any are nearby.
traits.name: agrizoophobe

traits.description:
Timmy is steadfastly loyal to his faction. he tries harder to get along with his compatriots and will never bail on them.

If imprisoned, he will be exceptionally uncooperative with his captors.
stats: Giving up and leaving mental state disabled.
Giving up and leaving mental state disabled.

traits.name: allegiant

traits.description: Timmy doesn't care for conversation. he doesn't chitchat with others, never engages in social recreation, and doesn't enjoy parties. he doesn't mind it when others slight or insult him - it's just words, after all.
traits.name: asocial

traits.description: Timmy could spend hours lost between the pages of a good book - he will feel happier after spending enough time reading. However, this preoccupation with reading has caused him to slightly neglect more physical pursuits.
traits.name: bookworm

traits.description: Timmy is driven to great heights by thoughts of those dear to him. he works harder, learns faster, and becomes more resistant to pain and stress based on the total strength of his positive relationships.
traits.name: champion

traits.description: Timmy is a master of small talk; speaking with others grants them a stacking mood bonus. If he goes on a mental break, it is likely to be an insulting spree.
traits.name: conversationalist

traits.description: Timmy has an overactive imagination. At random, or if he becomes too stressed, he will retreat into his imagination, resulting in a harmless mental break. After indulging his imagination in such a way, he becomes inspired.
traits.name: daydreamer

traits.description: Timmy is exceptionally skilled at basic tasks, but struggles with advanced concepts. Except for shooting, melee, and social, his skills degrade rapidly while above level 10.
traits.name: drudge

traits.description: Looking at corpses makes Timmy happy, and he doesn't mind wearing tainted apparel.
traits.name: graver

traits.description: Timmy is filled with vigor. he is difficult to harm, and is quick to bounce back from exhaustion, injury, and illness.
traits.name: hale

traits.description: Fun is everything to Timmy. he never gets bored of any kind of recreation, but he needs it more frequently than others.
traits.name: hedonist

traits.description: Timmy moves swiftly and lightly.
traits.name: hotfoot

traits.description: Timmy goes into exaggerated histrionics when below his mental break threshold, stressing out anyone who can see or hear him.
traits.name: hysteric

traits.description: Timmy is quick to assume the worst of other people. his opinions of others are much more strongly influenced by negative impressions than positive ones.
traits.name: judgemental

traits.description: Timmy really likes anyone he could be even a little attracted to. Sadly, the way in which he exhibits this is gross and creepy, so they tend not to like him back.
traits.name: lech

traits.description: Timmy needs someone to love with all his being. his mood soars immensely when he has a lover, but he is much more sensitive to romantic hurt, and those who spurn him also suffer.
traits.name: lovesick

traits.description: Timmy loves being in the water. he enjoys getting wet, and swims quite quickly.
traits.name: mariner

traits.description: Timmy has an inexplicably robust metabolism. he doesn't need to eat as often and never gets food poisoning. So long as the food isn't raw, he also doesn't care what it is.
stats: Binging on food mental state disabled.
Binging on food mental state disabled.

traits.name: metabolicfreak

traits.description: Roughing it out in the wilderness doesn't bother Timmy, but he despises being locked indoors.
traits.name: outdoorsy

traits.description: Timmy craves the approval of those he knows. he is happy when others like him, and sad when they don't.
traits.name: peoplepleaser

traits.description: Timmy harbors an extremely dangerous dark side which comes out when he starts to lose control. While stressed or in a mental break, he becomes much faster, stronger, and harder to subdue; during such an episode, any damage he takes may cause him to go berserk.
traits.name: repressedrage

traits.description: Timmy is all about the party life! he throws a party whenever he becomes inspired, and he loves attending any sort of social function.
traits.name: reveller

traits.description: Timmy gains mood and has a chance to become inspired when other people mentally break or socially fight. However, this tends not to endear him to those people.
traits.name: sadistic

traits.description: Timmy is quite adept at evading detection. he doesnt leave tracks and is difficult to spot. he even helps mask the passage of caravans he is part of.
traits.name: skulker

traits.description: Timmy can pick out targets at further distances than anyone else. However, he is less talented at close-quarters combat, and he feels unsafe without a ranged weapon.
traits.name: sniper

traits.description: Timmy lacks some sort of ineffable inner spark. he won't recreate, doesn't care for beauty, and can't become inspired.
traits.name: staid

traits.description: Timmy loves turbulent weather. he receives a slight mood boost when the weather acts up, and exotic conditions like eclipses, auroras, or even toxic fallout bring him great joy.
traits.name: tempestophile

traits.description: Timmy is utterly at peace. he will not participate in violence, and can't mentally break. Ever.
traits.name: tranquil

traits.description: Timmy is utterly at peace. he will not participate in violence, and can't mentally break. Ever.
traits.name: tranquil

traits.description:
Timmy doesnt feel the need to be in a community. If things get too bad, or if he experiences a random surge of wanderlust, he will leave.

If imprisoned, he will be uncooperative with his captors.
traits.name: vagabond

traits.description: Timmy is obsessed with his own appearance. his beauty and the quality of his apparel impact his mood.
traits.name: vain

traits.description: Violent intent builds up within Timmy, causing his mood to worsen until he unleashes it in a savage, lethal burst.
traits.name: vicious

traits.description: Timmy occasionally has episodes of profound insight during which he will create a schematic for a new technology. This happens more frequently when he is happier.
traits.name: visionary

traits.description: There's just something really likeable about Timmy.
traits.name: winsome

traits.description: Timmy has high expectations at minimum. When they are met, he loses motivation, so he works and learns slower.
traits.name: entitled

traits.description: Timmy has high expectations at minimum. When they are met, he becomes motivated, so he works and learns faster.
traits.name: prideful

traits.description: Timmy keeps his expectations low, no matter how pampered he gets. Even if he gains a position of authority, his expectations still won't progress past the moderate level.
traits.name: humble

traits.description: Timmy pays less attention to his senses than most. Though this is mostly disadvantageous, he can sleep soundly through anything, as well as weather more trying temperatures.
traits.name: imperceptive

traits.description: Timmy has very sharp senses. Though this is mostly a boon, it also makes him more sensitive to comfort, discomfort and extreme temperatures.
traits.name: keensenses

traits.description: Timmy has senses almost on par with bionic augmentation. Though this is mostly a boon, it also makes him more sensitive to comfort, discomfort and extreme temperatures.
traits.name: powerfulsenses

traits.description: Timmy hones his body to a state of notable physical fitness, allowing him to carry more and hit harder.
traits.name: mighty

traits.description: Timmy is immensely, ridiculously strong, allowing him to carry far more and hit far harder.
traits.name: herculean

traits.description: Timmy is so gullible it beggars belief. he is very strongly affected by his ideoligion, yet is also very susceptible to conversion attempts.
traits.name: overlycredulous

traits.description: Timmy believes almost anything anyone tells him. he is strongly affected by his ideoligion, yet is also susceptible to conversion attempts.
traits.name: credulous

traits.description: Timmy has nearly unshakable faith in his ideoligion. he is strongly affected by his ideoligion, and is very resistant to conversion attempts.
traits.name: adherent

traits.description: Timmy spends every breath in service of his ideoligion. he is very strongly affected by his ideoligion, and is immune to conversion attempts.
stats: Crisis of belief mental state disabled.
Crisis of belief mental state disabled.

traits.name: unquestioningadherent

traits.description: Timmy is chronically uncertain about everything; he is less affected by his ideoligion.
traits.name: doubtful

traits.description: Timmy dislikes and distrusts anyone who doesn't believe the things he does. Conversion attempts upset him, and changing to a new ideo frightens him terribly.
traits.name: intolerant

traits.description: Timmy tolerates those who dont follow his beliefs. he isn't quite so upset with non-believers who violate his ideoligion's taboos, and he isnt upset by botched conversion attempts.
traits.name: tolerant

traits.description: Timmy doesnt just want to be above others - he needs others to be far beneath him. he can be satisfied by holding a position of authority or by the presence of enough slaves.
traits.name: subjugator

traits.description:
Timmy believes freedom is a right everyone should enjoy. he disapproves of slavery, and, to a lesser extent, imprisonment of anyone he knows.

If imprisoned, he will be uncooperative with his captors.
traits.name: liberator

traits.description: For Timmy, maintaining ideoligious solidarity is more important than embracing the truth. he will never be in the ideoligious minority for longer than two days; he then converts to whatever the most people in the faction he belongs to (or is enslaved by) believes.
traits.name: conformist

traits.description: Timmy projects a sense of wisdom, allowing him to use the abilities of a moral guide. If he actually has the moral guide role, he will have two copies of the ability set, on separate cooldowns.
traits.name: guru

traits.description: Timmy feels restless and unhappy when his ideoligion is in the majority. Conversely, he works harder and is more determined when in the minority.
traits.name: persecutioncomplex

traits.description: Timmy is very eager to convert others to his ideoligion.
traits.name: proclaimer

traits.description: Timmy constantly questions the nature and purpose of reality, personhood, and other profound topics. As a result, he may randomly come up with a new ideoligion, which he will be very passionate about spreading.
traits.name: radicalthinker

traits.description: Timmy believes in a wide variety of superstitions. As he randomly comes across what he believes to be omens, his mood will fluctuate.
traits.name: superstitious

traits.description: Timmy really dislikes and distrusts children and pregnant people.
traits.name: misopedist

traits.description: Timmy believes that children are the most important thing in the universe. he enjoys taking care of them; living in a place without kids makes him feel empty.
traits.name: caretaker

traits.description: Timmy likes having mechanoids around. he will be saddened if an allied mechanoid dies.
traits.name: mechaphile

traits.description: Timmy hates mechanoids, and he dislikes and distrusts those who control them. This antipathy is so strong that he can project it to discombobulate mechanoids, provided he has the means to broadcast on their bandwidth.
traits.name: mechaphobe

traits.description: Timmy thinks the beauty and health of the land should be preserved. he despises pollution, and appreciates being anywhere without its taint.
traits.name: environmentalist

traits.description: Timmy takes any opportunity he can to arm others with knowledge. Whenever he socially interacts with someone, they gain experience in a random skill both parties can use.
traits.name: mentor

traits.description: Timmy really dislikes and distrusts those of different xenotypes. he may not mind variation in the genetics of his own kind, but even xenotypes very similar to his own are disgusting in his eyes.
traits.name: xenotypist

traits.description:
Buy Tynan's book. Otherwise, you'll find out that his melee dps and armor penetration are over NINE THOUSAND!!1!

(Timmy isn't actually any better at doing damage).
traits.name: gamedeveloper

traits.description: Timmy's mother didn't rase no loser. Timmy will tough it out and roll with the punches life thows at them.
traits.name: mammadidn'traisealoser

traits.description: Timmy's mother rase a loser. Timmy will complain and give up on most of the problems life thows at them.
traits.name: mammaraisedaloser

traits.description: Timmy has always had an ungodly affinity for fighting.
traits.name: tenaciousfighter

traits.description: Timmy has always been a natural at fighting whether it be with ranged weapons, melee or just strait throwing hands.
traits.name: goodfighter

traits.description: Timmy has never been a good fighter. No matter how hard they work on their combat skills they are outclassed by people with the same or less training then them.
traits.name: badfighter

traits.description: Timmy has always known how to interact with and befriend animals.
traits.name: animalwhisperer

traits.description: Timmy is very charismatic they can usualy talk to and negotiate with people well.
traits.name: charismatic

traits.description: Timmy can work with plants better than most people.
traits.name: greenthumb

traits.description: Timmy can't work with plants well, They preform poorly to anything plant related no matter how good their knowledge about plants are.
traits.name: blackthumb

traits.description: Timmy's body produces tremendous ammounts of heat. They are not bothered by temperatures which would send onother inot shivers, but they also dont like heat.
traits.name: hot-skinned

traits.description: Timmy is naturally warm and handles cool temperatures better than most.
traits.name: warm-skinned

traits.description: Timmy is a human icicle and loves hot weather- but doesn't handle cold very well.
traits.name: icy-skinned

traits.description: Timmy is naturally cool and handles warm temperatures better than most.
traits.name: cool-skinned

traits.description: Timmy was born with a physically weak body and injuries that would give one person a semmi-bad bruse will give Timmy a broken bone.
traits.name: glassbones

traits.description: Timmy's brain is wired difrently and releases an excess amount of dopamine all the time. Timmy is always supper happy but when things finally hit the fan for them, they are prone to loosing it quickly.
traits.name: hyperhappy

traits.description: Timmy's brain is wired diffrently and wont release a healthy amount of dopamine resulting in unyielding depression. Over the years Timmy has developed an Ironclad resolve as a makeshift way to manage the saddness
traits.name: dopaminedeprived

traits.description: Timmy is built like a mule, they have an extremely strong back this alows them to carry more wheight than others. Timmy's Iron back also alows them to sleep on the ground with no repercussions.
traits.name: ironback

traits.description: Timmy has a slow metabolisim and takes longer to process food.
traits.name: slowmetabolisim

traits.description: Timmy has a fast metabolisim and processes food quickly.
traits.name: fastmetabolisim

traits.description: Timmy places great importance on the wearing of garments. he dislikes being naked, and thinks poorly of others for not covering up at all times. he also can't stand wearing tattered apparel, so he takes good care of his apparel.
traits.name: textile

traits.description: Timmy is a pure-blood Wolfein.
traits.name: pure-bloodwolfein

traits.description: Timmy is a biotic god.
traits.name: bioticgod

traits.description: Timmys biotic capabilities are significantly dampened by past trauma, or simply the lack of predisposition.
traits.name: bioticallydeaf

traits.description: Timmy has not yet unlocked their full biotic potential, and most likely never will.
traits.name: bioticallydull

traits.description: Timmys biotic skills are greatly above average, allowing them to use the power without any fear of migraines or discomfort.
traits.name: bioticallyskilled

traits.description: Timmys biotic skills are known far and wide across the galaxy due to their talent and rare predisposition.
traits.name: bioticallytalented

traits.description: Timmy is a Demon of the Night Winds.
traits.name: ardatyakshi

races.description:
Anties are genetically engineered beings by a private company to replace dying soldiers on the battle field.

Everything has gone south when the company has let their guard down to celebrate their recent progress. Due to a mistake made by one of the employees, the Anties have been set free from the lab and ended up in space.

Their personalities are gentle by nature, but they were made to know only but war. On each planet they end up, they burn everything down to ash, using themselves as the main source of the fuel.

Anty is hermaphrodite, has no externally exposed reproductive organs, but has both a scrotum and ovaries in the abdomen.

Anty's gender is indicated based on her reproductive system, which was a little more developed prior to consuming the Nutritional jelly.

The average height of common anty ergates and queen ants is 140cm, while soldier ants are 170cm. Depending on needs or the type of hive, it can transform or grow up to 200cm.
races.name: Anty

races.description: A baseline human, mostly unmodified by gene engineering and mostly unchanged by evolutionary pressures on non-Earth planets.
races.name: human

races.description: An all-female race of humans spliced with fox genes. Originally, they were Glitterworld designermates from the planet Aolara, but an internal war forced them to leave their homeworld. Now they are spread among the rim.
races.name: Kurin

races.description: A hybrid with DNA from a human and an orassan. Typically created through careful genetic engineering in a lab, or the "natural" way from individuals with closely regulated gene mods, these hybrids combine some of the best traits from their parent species. The particular traits and physical characteristics that are being inherited are typically chosen by the parents having the child, but they almost always have two feline ears and a feline tail, both with fur sharing the same color as the hair on their head.
races.name: neko

races.description: A baseline orassan, mostly unmodified by gene engineering and mostly unchanged by evolutionary pressures on non-Orassia planets. A mammalian humanoid feline race. Evolving in cold caves and life on space ships make it so they don't mind the dark or being inside for long periods of time.
races.name: orassan

races.description: Inhabitants of lunar cities that carry the genes of rabbits, the rabbie excel at waging war and constructing mega-cities. They travel the galaxy in search of celestial bodies with planetarium; a drug that the rabbie population has been reliant on for survival since the begining of their history. It is believed they originally came from another galaxy, but have sinced lost the technology and have been cut off from their home galaxy.
races.name: Rabbie

races.description:
They are bioweapons recreated after Mechanoids by the Anties.

Dreadnaughts are possessed only the most advanced Hives and are stationed at the last lines of defense.

They are equipped with low-angle intercepting systems. Unlike low-angle shields, they deny both incoming and outgoing projectiles.(Dlc) 

If the dreadnaughts are seen on the battlefront, it means child's play is over.
races.name: Anty Dreadnought

races.description:
A humanoid race living in cities under the sea. Having traits similar to sea creatures, their blood contains substances that can be used for various medicaluses.

Descendants of glitterworld explorers who settled in the deep sea, generations of body modifications have led to their current form. Spreading far and wide into the rim, they built many cities and prospered. Until now.
races.name: Moyo

races.description: Designer mates are genetically engineered on glitterworlds to be the perfect mate. This is a decendant of one of them that still inherits most of the traits.
races.name: designer mate

races.description: A genetically modified human. Either through gene therapy or environmental pressure this kind of human has developed a think leathery skin. Scalemen are slightly slower and tire quicker than normal humans but they are highly adapted to hot biomes, need less food and have some natural armor.
races.name: Scaleman

races.description: A genetically altered human usually breed for combat. Soldiermorphs feel less pain, are tougher and need less food. However they have a very low life expectancy and learn new things slower than an average human.
races.name: soldiermorph

races.description: A genetically altered version of the baseline human. This wolflike human has altered hands with retractable claws capable of inflicting serious damage. Animallike instincts are more present in this person and wolfmen often have a short fuse and are easy to anger.
races.name: wolfman

races.description: Including the 'Ordinary', the common ancestor of Miho is a "Red Fox", not a human. Of course, this is not due to natural evolution but is presumed to be the result of uplift by an unknown transcendent being. This means they look like humans but are not actually human. They have an "Elegans" linked with mechanites in their bodies, which determines the strength of their psychic powers depending on the amount of sunlight. Because of this organ, these foxes pray to the sun and energy.
races.name: Miho

races.description:
They are bioweapons recreated after Mechanoids by the Anties.
\Hive guard are possessed only the most advanced Hives and are stationed at the last lines of defense.

They are equipped with High-angle intercepting systems. Unlike High-angle shields, they deny both incoming and outgoing projectiles.(Dlc) 

If the Hive guard are seen on the battlefront, it means child's play is over.
races.name: Anty Hive guard

races.description:
They are bioweapons recreated after Mechanoids by the Anties.
\Tri-Jaws are possessed only the most advanced Hives and are stationed at the last lines of defense.

They are equipped with A powerful red burst laser weapon can be fired at up to 2 people, and can be fired at 1 person while moving.

If the Tri-Jaws are seen on the battlefront, it means child's play is over.
races.name: Anty Tri-Jaw

races.description: It is a human like a rodent gene. Although the origin is unknown, it is a monarchy society based on agricultural society. There are more female objects than males, and it is difficult to distinguish the gender of the object when viewed from the outside.
races.name: Ratkin

races.description: It is a human like a rodent gene. Although the origin is unknown, it is a monarchy society based on agricultural society. There are more female objects than males, and it is difficult to distinguish the gender of the object when viewed from the outside.
races.name: Ratkin subject

races.description:
A race of humanlike robots.

The origins of these machines are mostly unknown. Some speculate they are escapees from a civilization that used them for labor, and some suggest they are outdated pleasure models that got dumped by a passing space freighter.

By design from their previous masters they are physically weak, but their raw fortitude is enough to make up for it. Beware of their biological reactor that violently explode if they die from overheating.
races.name: android

races.description:
A race of rudimentary humanlike worker robots.

Usually found toiling in colonies around the rim that has a resident tinkerer.

While not capable of sapience, their relatively cheap cost and ability to work around the clock make them valuable workers.

Droids are not born and must be created.
races.name: droid

races.description:
A race of rudimentary humanlike warrior robots.

Usually found guarding the homes of the wealthy and offices of mega corporations, they show no mercy upon targets who fail to identify themselves. Traditionally armed with miniguns and light machine guns.

Droids are not born and must be created.
races.name: battle droid

races.description:
A race of archotech humanlike worker robots.

Usually found toiling around in colonies around the rim which got archotech level tech. Capable of sentience to a degree, allowing them to research, train animals and even speak though they will not benefit from conversation. 

Archodroids are at their peak, outperforming even humans. 

Droids are not born and must be created.
races.name: ArchoDroid

races.description:
A race of archotech humanlike warrior robots.

Installed into military bases and highly sensitive areas. They show no mercy upon targets who fail to identify themselves and are traditionally armed with miniguns and core launchers.

Destroyers are at their peak in power and defensive capabilities. Destroyers possess four arms, each of which is highly deadly. Humans beware: bring an army to defeat this model.

Droids are not born and must be created.
races.name: Destroyer

races.description:
A race of spacer-tech humanlike worker robots.

Usually found toiling in colonies around the rim that has a resident tinkerer. Not being capable of sapience makes them perfect for colony tasks.

Advanced droids are much better than their outdated models in every way.

Droids are not born and must be created.
races.name: advanced droid

races.description:
A race of spacer-tech humanlike warrior robots.

Installed into military bases and highly sensitive areas, they show no mercy upon targets who fail to identify themselves. Traditionally armed with miniguns and light machine guns.

Advanced droids are much better than their outdated models in every way. Wardroids possess four arms, each of which is highly deadly. Humans beware: bring an army to defeat this model.

Droids are not born and must be created.
races.name: wardroid

races.description: Small drone constructed of simple materials built in a short time. This device is masterful in building & mining, but is unable to do much else. Cannot fight.
races.name: engineer

races.description: Small drone constructed of simple materials built in a short time. This device is masterful in tasks relating to food & farming, but is unable to do much else. Cannot fight.
races.name: chef

races.description: Small drone constructed of simple materials built in short time. This drone is highly capable in medicine and in taking care of most injuries, but is unable to do much else. Cannot fight.
races.name: medic

races.description: Small drone constructed of simple materials built in short time. This device is masterful in tasks relating to hauling and transportation of goods by caravan, but is unable to do much else. Cannot fight.
races.name: transport

races.description: Small drone constructed of simple materials built in short time. This device is equipped with a basic AI that allows it to research, but is unable to do much else. Cannot fight.
races.name: think tank

races.description: Small drone constructed of simple materials built in short time. This device is masterful in Ranching, but is unable to do much else. Cannot fight.
races.name: rancher

races.description: Small single use drone built in short time. Only good for fighting large fires. Cannot fight.
races.name: dum-E

races.description: Small drone constructed of simple materials built in short time. This device is masterful in tasks relating to fabrication and smithing, but is unable to do much else. Cannot fight.
races.name: assembly

races.description:
Matching the simplicity of their purpose, the simplicity of the grunt drone's design is its greatest feature. Designed purely for work, they are durable, capable, and persistent. Lacking the fine motor controls of less hyper-specialized designs, though, they are incapable of most complex tasks.

The most advanced elements of its design are its batteries and generators, which allow it to maximize its workflow and minimize downtime.
races.name: synstruct grunt

races.description:
Overseer drones are intimidating beings, inhuman and alien. With a single limb reaching from their spindly torso affixed with needle-like appendages, a trio of visual sensors that emit uncomfortable light, and an affixing stare, overseers are the scrying and analytical extensions of their masters. Capable of carrying out research tasks and the vital task of reprogramming and mending broken machinery, overseers are critical components in the massive scale machinery of fully automated drone hives.

While some believe them to have inscrutable sapience, they are still drones, and follow whatever programming they possess. Drones reprogramming drones is a nightmare for many, and overseer drones are often hunted for this very reason.

Their hyperspecialized design and sheer innate complexity leaves precious little room for much else.
races.name: synstruct overseer

races.description:
Mouthpieces of paranoid dictators, messengers of lords and organizations, diplomatic units between warring factions, envoys are the forward and expendable faces of those they serve. Without fear for self and no ability to be autonomous or to incite rebellion, these units form the cornerstone of any survival-oriented figurehead's public outreach programs. Fragile and unthreatening, these units rely on the vast apparatus of charismatic voices and personas encoded within them to cajole, convert, subvert, or simply relay messages to others. Unusual for a RimWorld given their cost relative to their value, envoys are rarely witnessed beyond the service of highly advanced drone hives or Ultratech wanderers.

While nominally designed for social tasks alone, they are versatile enough to perform tasks that do not require brute strength.
races.name: synstruct envoy

races.description:
A suit of intricately inscribed and psychically imbued metal armor animated by a cloud of chemfuel-consuming mechanites that dwell within the suit as if using it as a shell. When not under the psychic command of a higher intelligence, Mechcloud chemwalkers will wander aimlessly in search of the chemfuel necessary to sustain themselves.

Primitive societies often refer to them as "buzzing armor" due to the unsettling sound of the mechanite swarm rattling inside the armor - and often believe the armor to be possessed by spirits that can be communed with.

More sophisticated societies recognize that there is nothing magical or spiritual about these entities, but rather that they are animated by a cloud of millions of microscopic - but quite powerful - mechanites that can be dominated by an individual who can call upon psychic influence.
races.name: mechcloud chemwalker

races.description:
A superhumanly massive suit of elaborately inscribed and psychically imbued metal armor animated by a ravenous swarm of chemfuel-consuming mechanites that dwell within the suit as if using it as a shell. When not under the psychic command of a higher intelligence, lumbering chemwalkers will wander aimlessly in search of the chemfuel necessary to sustain themselves.

Primitive societies often refer to them as "stormcloud golems" due to the incessant rattling sound of the mechanite swarm swirling inside the armor like a raging tempest - often believing that only dread warlords or powerful heroes can possess a spirit capable of inhabiting and wielding such a construct.

More sophisticated societies recognize that there is nothing magical or spiritual about these entities, but rather that they are animated by a cloud of millions of microscopic - but quite powerful - mechanites that can be dominated by an individual who can call upon psychic influence.
races.name: lumbering chemwalker

races.description:
Synstruct warriors are the standard baseline for fully autonomous combat drones - cheap, durable, and powerful. These are units crafted for war and war alone, and they are very good at it.

Its small, box-like shape earned it the nicknames of "battle-box" and "blaster-bucket," while its default red paint color and military role earned it the affectionate name "Redcoat." The unusual shape also prevents wearing humanlike apparel.

Synstruct warriors may be formatted into the following types:
 - Drones
 - Reprogrammable drones
races.name: synstruct warrior

races.description:
Bishops vaguely resemble humans from afar unlike warriors or paladins, albeit ones that are unusually tall and thin. With six limbs that interchangeably act as legs and arms and backup internalized visual sensors, these slender war units are exceedingly tough to incapacitate. Where warriors are cheap and quick to assemble, bishops favor quality and rapid dynamism. These are units crafted for combat, both defensively and offensively, and can hold or push a line with steely determination.

Due to their thin build and considerable height, they have earned the nicknames "deathstick" and "warpole," while their distinctive "head" segment is the source of their common name.

Synstruct bishops may be formatted into the following types:
 - Drones
 - Reprogrammable drones
 - Sapients
races.name: synstruct bishop

races.description:
The very first combat variant idealized, blueprinted, and created by artifical intelligences alone, the paladin design is as unique as it is aesthetically lacking: a rectangular prism with two forward arms and four large manipulators. It has a very odd design choice: rather than being heavily armored to prevent taking damage, paladins instead have a highly reactive hyperweave-infused chassis that significantly reduces incoming damage. The more damage it sustains, the more resilient against damage it becomes - making each paladin a warfighting champion. Specialized hardware vastly increases rate of fire.

The earliest paladins - contrary to expectation - took to their military role eagerly, and quickly developed a militaristic worldview that often is likened to ancient chivalric customs. Duels, ritualistic combat, and contempt for civilians are common. While paladins exhibit no strong moralistic tendencies as a group, violence should be expected from individuals that are insulted or suffer breakdowns.

Due to their large size and shape, they earned the nickname "Warwagon" - but the proud paladins demand to be referred to by their self-given name. Few are brave enough to challenge their choice. Many have died for making unflattering comparisons between paladins and mechanoid centipedes.

Synstruct paladins may be formatted into the following types:
 - Sapients
races.name: synstruct paladin

races.description:
Jellymen were an accident, originally borne of an ultratech society's misadventure with archotech research. This semi-gelatinous mass of mechanites takes human form, and has a plethora of odd properties. Devoid of coolant and distinct limbs, uniquely psychically gifted with a very human-like brain that can absorb archotech devices like mechlinks and neuroformers, possessed of a body that reacts to harm like paladins do, immune to overheating and freezing, and even able to eject a mass of mechanites to incapacitate a foe in close combat, these are powerful beings indeed. The process for their creation is not well understood - but raving prophets claim these agglomerates are hierophants, and can be "naturally born" by the true gift of the archotechs.

Despite everything, as a group, they behave like and have the desires of normal individuals. The given name for their kind does not bother them as long as they can participate in society on equal terms.
races.name: synstruct jellyman

races.description:
The juggernaut is a testament both to human engineering and the folly of their ambition. Assembling one requires a production facility with instruments of picoscoping precision and timeliness, an interstellar empire's worth of logistical supply, and repeated blasts that could level a city and leave a subcontinent uninhabitable for decades. Manufactured more for prestige and demonstrations of wealth than for actual combat capability, juggernauts should be extremely rare to find beyond the arsenals of glitterworlds.

Curiously, though, rogue juggernauts can be found floating through space with alarming frequency. It is unclear where they are coming from, but it is well-known that one making landfall heralds chaos. They do not belong on RimWorlds, and are entirely unserviceable here. The countless flaws in their design, ranging from simple internal oversights to just how much logistics are required to keep them operational in the long-run, make them fundamentally unsuited to surviving any length of time.

Juggernauts are even designed to violently and explosively self-destruct rather than be salvageable, making them effectively worthless for anything other than throwing at enemies. While they are marvels to behold, and could constitute one of the single most dangerous entities to encounter, they are derided by most all who know of them.
races.name: synstruct juggernaut

races.description:
Synstruct simpletons are widely derided by everyone who meets them. Every aspect of them is designed to be as minimalistic and simple as possible - and not in a good way. Other sapient synstructs are especially hostile toward sapient simpletons, seeing them as an insult to their kind. Simpletons are usually created only out of desperation or cruelty. Sapient simpletons often embrace the wretchedness of their existence and seek to prove themselves equals to others or go on paths of wrathful vengeance against their creators. Simpleton drones, of course, do not pay any heed to their own wellbeing, being incapable of thought as they are.

Synstruct simpletons may be formatted into the following types:
 - Drones
 - Reprogrammable drones
 - Sapients
races.name: synstruct simpleton

races.description:
Synstruct commoners are, unsurprisingly, the most common model of synstruct in civil society. They are almost identical in capability and nature to humans - a fact sapient commoners pride themselves on. Like humans, commoners can be found taking almost any path through life, and excel at no one particular aspect of it. Like all sapient synstructs, though, heroic figures and pariahs alike have counted themselves among the commoners' kind, and have risen and fallen in public view with time - all to prove that even the most basic form of synstruct can ascend well past their manufacturer's intent.

Synstruct commoners may be formatted into the following types:
 - Drones
 - Reprogrammable drones
 - Sapients
races.name: synstruct commoner

races.description:
Synstruct stoics are designed to be rugged and hardy individuals. With a great deal of internal systems made to stand up to the test of time, they make ideal survivalists, pioneers, and rebels. Stoics are largely a reserved and perceptive lot, more prone to listening than speaking, and are often disdainful of those who break down mentally under stress. Like all sapient synstructs, though, outliers and renegades exist - many of whom are notorious outlaws, anarchists, monastic firebrands, and intergalactic explorers.

Synstruct stoics may be formatted into the following types:
 - Sapients
races.name: synstruct stoic

races.description:
Synstruct socialites are designed with communal living in mind and have systems meticulously theorized around evolving social situations. Most socialites embrace their model's design philosophy and are gregarious and extroverted individuals who revel both in tightly knit groups and massive anonymous crowds. Like all sapient synstructs, though, outliers and renegades exist that undermine the otherwise noble reputation.

Synstruct socialites may be formatted into the following types:
 - Sapients
races.name: synstruct socialite

races.description: The mysterious horned and feathered humanoid found on some rim worlds, Oni are often sought out by Glitterworlds for their beauty as a sort of exotic pet. Worse still some are kept as livestock for their feathers, pelts and horns, all having pratical and decorative uses. Oni live in temperate areas and rarely employ clothing due to the uncomfortable sensation on their feathered bodies.
races.name: Oni

races.description: The ancient ancestors of the current Oni that can be found on some rim worlds. They have been mysteriously appearing with no traceable origins, but their descendant race welcomes them into their tribes without question.
races.name: Ancestral Oni

races.description:
A flak jacket, pants, and helmet imprinted and imbued with psychic power animated by a cloud of chemfuel-consuming mechanites that dwell within the apparel as if using it as a shell. When not under the psychic command of a higher intelligence, flakker chemwalkers will wander aimlessly in search of the chemfuel necessary to sustain themselves.

Primitive societies are generally terrified by what they call "poltergeist warriors" due to the uncanny featureless mass of the mechanites that resembling a shifting gray shadow that is visible protruding from the flak armor.

More sophisticated societies recognize that there is nothing magical or spiritual about these entities, but rather that they are animated by a cloud of millions of microscopic - but quite powerful - mechanites that can be dominated by an individual who can call upon psychic influence and call these particular entities "flakkers" due to the flak jacket they inhabit.

It is a mystery as to how the Mechcloud understands which part of the helmet should be facing forward - and why the Mechcloud chooses to hoist it so far above the jacket.
races.name: flak chemwalker

races.description:
A suit of intricately inscribed and psychically imbued power armor animated by a cloud of chemfuel-consuming mechanites that dwell within the suit as if using it as a shell. When not under the psychic command of a higher intelligence, marine chemwalkers will wander aimlessly in search of the chemfuel necessary to sustain themselves.

Primitive societies see these "ghosts from the stars" as suits of magical armor possessed by spirits of those who came from beyond their world to continue in death what they did in life.

More sophisticated societies recognize that there is nothing magical or spiritual about these entities, but rather that they are animated by a cloud of millions of microscopic - but quite powerful - mechanites that can be dominated by an individual who can call upon psychic influence.
races.name: marine chemwalker

races.description:
Prestige recon armor imprinted with control sigils animated by a cloud of chemfuel-consuming mechanites that dwell within the apparel as if using it as a shell. When not under the psychic command of a higher intelligence, eltex chemwalkers will wander aimlessly in search of the chemfuel necessary to sustain themselves.

Primitive societies fear these "magi from the stars" which emit an unsettling keening noise and which are capable of low level psychic powers.

Even sophisticated societies generally find eltex chemwalkers to be bordering on the occult, for the eltex embedded into the recon armor gives them access to seemingly unnatural capabilities that are difficult to explain - despite the fact that they are in fact like any other chemwalker.

Sometimes, if one stares at an eltex chemwalker for long enough, they get an uncanny sensation that an foreign, alien presence influences - but never directly commands - the ever-shifting and otherwise obedient mechanite swarm.
races.name: eltex chemwalker

races.description:
A suit of intricately inscribed and psychically imbued cataphract armor animated by a cloud of chemfuel-consuming mechanites that dwell within the suit as if using it as a shell. When not under the psychic command of a higher intelligence, cataphract chemwalkers will wander aimlessly in search of the chemfuel necessary to sustain themselves.

Given the full seal that these suits provide, few can tell that these chemwalkers are not people at first. The only giveaway is the quiet rattling of millions of mechanites coursing through the armor, which can easily be waved off as machinery within the suit. It only becomes clear that there is no one inside once the armor is removed and the mechanites escape - or when the chemwalker, which lacks the ability to speak, fails to communicate when expected.
races.name: cataphract chemwalker

races.description: However, as prosperity inevitably leads to decline, this civilization did not escape the fate of destruction. The Thucydides Trap led to a great war between two totalitarian regimes on this planet. The outcome of this war has long been lost to history, but one of its most direct consequences was a series of explosions at a nuclear power plant cluster in Siberia, part of the 'Eurasian Common Defense Agreement Alliance.' The massive energy and radioactive materials released from the explosions accidentally awakened a dormant avatar of an Other god deep within the planet (note: to be verified). The awakening of this Other god resulted in two chain reactions: first, the entire Siberian region and parts of Central Asia transformed into enclosed area, making them inaccessible and unobservable from the outside; second, those who were trapped inside the enclosed area, fortunate enough to have survived the war and the 'awakening,' underwent inhuman mutations. The modern scientific community unanimously agrees that these mutated humans are the original 'cinders.'
races.name: Cinder

races.description: A genetically engineered son of the God Emperor of Man.
races.name: primarch

races.description:
The Wolfein are a nocturnal humanoid species, gifted with night vision and hearing far superior to that of humans. Their most distinctive features are the lupine ears atop their heads and the fluffy wolf tails at their backs. Today, the entire race lives under the iron rule of a megacorp known as the Military-Industrial Combinea colossal enterprise that once served as the Wolfein Empires defense contractor and has since permeated every stage of Wolfein life, from birth to death.

            Though Wolfein civilization has advanced into the space age, the instinct for rebellion inherited through generations of wolf-blooded genes is steadily being dismantled by the corporate machine. The vast majority of Wolfein now curl beneath the megacorps totalitarian rule, their lives dissected into quantifiable data units by an omnipresent, unblinking surveillance system. Even the faintest thought of escape is swiftly erased within the airtight net of control.

            After a brutal total war with the Machinekind decimated the Wolfein population, the megacorp's grip began to show cracks. To fill the void in combat strength, it reverse-engineered Machinekind technology and mass-produced efficient killing machines. Amidst the ruins of war, a resistance movement has begun to grow in the shadows. Bound by the creed overthrow the megacorp at all costs, their actionslabeled as acts of terrorism by official mediaare now tearing fissures into the rusted iron curtain of corporate control.
races.name: Wolfein race

races.description: The legacy of a fallen empire, with a distant link to the humanoid races of earth and beyond. Other than the fact that they began to awaken over the past century, no one knows much else about what they are, where they are from or fundamentals behind their technology, which seems to bridge the gap between science and magic.
races.name: forsaken

races.description: The Nightkin were an elite warrior caste in the Master's super mutant army and the apex of his creation of super mutants. When the Master's super mutant army was defeated in 2162, many began wandering the wasteland or banded together into groups of varying sizes and with varying ends.
races.name: Nightkin

races.description: Super mutant is a general term referring to humanoid mutants created by exposing a regular and relatively unmutated human to a variant of the Forced Evolutionary Virus (FEV). The resulting hulking mutants typically possess exceptional strength, endurance, resistance or immunity to disease and radiation, as well as modified intelligence.
races.name: Supermutant

races.description: A non feral ghoul, is a decrepit, rotting, zombie-like mutant. Intense and prolonged radiation has ravaged their skin, much of their flesh and in some cases many of their ligaments.
races.name: ghoul

races.description: A non-feral glowing ghoul, is a decrepit, rotting, zombie-like mutant. Intense and prolonged radiation has ravaged their skin, much of their flesh and in some cases many of their ligaments. It emits a powerful glow capable of growing plants.
races.name: glowing one
